12/06/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The State Service for National Security (DANS) announced on Thursday (June 11th) that its agents have arrested a businessman who offered a 50,000-euro bribe to a high-ranking public official. 
The businessman was identified only as R.M. 
from the Avto Engineering company. 
He reportedly was caught offering the bribe to a public servant, who refused to accept it. 
(Focus, TV Europe, AFP, Reuters - 11/06/09)
